objects.text:
[you find yourself in a strange building unsure of where you are. the room you're in is beautiful and regal. As you look around you eventually see a tall woman with a strange ethereal glow around her no matter how hard you try and see her you can't quite discern her features. just as you try and sneak away she spots you.] 
Hello is someone there? you're not supposed to be here. this isn't supposed to happen. Hm? Well? off you go. I know it's not the door you came from but you know what I don't really care. I don't care, and it's not my problem so off you go. I hope to never see you again. please leave now. 
[you suddenly disappear as quickly as you arrived as she pushes you through a door and everything goes black]

[you wake up in a Haybale, dressed in a strangely patterned kimono. once you get out of the bale you find a piece of paper tied to the bottom of the bright fabric] 

 "Hello, I guess I should explain some things. Who I am is not important but just know that I am part of the Multiversal analog recording society (m.a.r.s for short) we are a group for recording, analyzing, and sorting any universe created by the stories thought of and told by inhabitants of your old dimension. That's right your stories really have that much power. We call these 'FICTASPHEREs' But anyway let me get back on track. you are a wanderer. wanderers are beings like you who "slip" between the cracks of your world. Normally our sorting systems would catch anyone who slipped and would sort them back into their dimension but for some reason, you must've slipped past the system and wound up in my court. Now if I had my way what I did would have been fine, but  APpAReNtLy, I'm not allowed to throw any wanderers into whatever Fictasphere door is nearest. How was I supposed to know there were protocols for things like this, but seriously it's not like anyone will even _#2!$%$#5~`~~```~@`#~~3~djois~~~not like its ~~~~~ no one will m1~~ them 32reffre#4%$%^75&^&*%&$%7%$^R&and I|'s not like Cr*#@s is even going to find out  645*&^%8*((57#$?./'":'">:\|{:sf
a]\qwe3@!#$%43526"

[the note goes on for the rest of the tag but the writing is too smudged and the letters you can read are written in a hasty and illegible script anyway... after you hit the bottom of the page you turn over and the writing becomes legible again]

"But anyways I need to explain what's happening before I run out of space. You have been sent to the world of demon slayer. If you saw the show back when you were in your dimension then you know what you're up against(and no I can't just send you back I could've if I hadn't sent you through the gate but...oh well...heh sorry.). In case you haven't seen the show let me introduce you to your new home for the rest of your (hopefully not too short) life. This is the world of Demon Slayer. Decades ago a man named Muzan was turned into a horrible creature of the night called a demon. In this world demons are somewhat a mix between cannibal vampires and very buff magicians. Even the weakest of demons is about 5 times stronger than your average human and more powerful demons have special abilities called Blood Demon Arts that can create a myriad of different effects and attacks. The only thing stopping these demons from rampaging all over this country is the might of the Demon Slayer Corps. The corp is composed of multiple ranks and their entire job is to brave the attacks of demons. Now since you were supposed to do something important in your dimension that would have further advanced society, you must do your best to do the same in this world. So joining the Slayer Corps is a must. Even if you try not to join something will force you to join. Now I can't send you in completely unprepared so I'm going to gift you with a couple of boons. There are two types that I have to give you. Immutable boons which my boss is making me give so you don't mess up the fabric of this universe or die unexpectedly, and there are also soul boons which take that energy from your soul, its complexity, and its potential and diffuse it into items, abilities, and knowledge that you will gain. I have to give you soul boons since the stored-up energy of your soul could tear you and this world apart if most of it isn't channeled. Now let's get this creation over with"

[As you finish reading the note you realize that you aren't fully *there* yet. Your outfit exists, but the "thing" inside it is pure energy. You have no true form yet. As you realize this, boxes and text appear before your face, prompting you to read them and make choices that will bring you more fully into this world as a real living person]

TL:dr- you're in the world of Demon Slayer and are about to join the corps.

rows.title: Immutable boons
rows.titleText:
"Due to the fact that your soul isn't a one to one match for the ones in this world we'll have to give you some abilities that come standard with native souls so you don't stick out like a sore thumb.I also have to give you some boons that will help the world fabric not break."

[These are the boons that you are stuck with no matter what. They will all usually be a help to you and will not draw any more attention to you than if you didn't have them unless otherwise stated]

objects.title: Does that even exist here?
objects.text: "This boon gets rid you of any pre-existing illness, mobility issues,chronic fatigue,etc"

objects.title: Determination
objects.text: "This ability will allow you to weather through small amounts of pain during battles or training without noticing. I'd say about five times as much as you could in your past life. It's still equal to what people in this world can take though, and you'll feel it once you're done with the fight."

objects.title: Continue to live
objects.text:
"We can't have you dipping out on us early. With this boon, you won't die of anything small such as disease, food poisoning, unfortunate accidents, etc. There are also minor other things too that aren't big enough to mention." 

[you will not die from anything that isn't actively attempting to kill you old age, viruses, bacteria, or the consequences of your own stupid actions gone awry]

objects.title: Backstory
objects.text: "Alright usually if this had been done properly I would have been able to offer you the choice to create yourself but due to my 'rule-breaking,' I can only make you a Harper Whozat. you'll be utterly average in this world until you start living in it. So sorry if you were really strong or good-looking originally. Though luckily you can change some things that still keep you in that generic range such as age, race,gender, and things like that. "

objects.title: Full Recovery
objects.text:
"This boon helps you to recover after taking serious damage. If you get proper medical attention and plenty of rest you should be able to recover from anything as long as you take enough time to heal. Though that might be years or decades depending on the injury" 
[This ability is not regeneration. You cannot regrow limbs or organs or anything that major. But if someone found a way to graft a spare limb on, or something similar then you're body would heal and accept the part without any major complications]

objects.title: Canon Compliance
objects.text: "This boon is one that I need to know more than you do, but I should still explain. Now that you're in a fictasphere you will always find something happening. Events and problems will always find their way to you eventually. this is because your strong soul has marked you as a main character. Luckily my boss was able to get your soul diverted to an offshoot, which is what happens when someone writes fan materials of a pre-existing fictasphere. So people in your world won't notice any changes in their Anime and now all of your adventures will be chronicled in what seems like an unread fanfic that no one in your world will question. This also means you can disrupt the plot without risking a breach in the walls of reality"

rows.title: "You"
rows.titleText:
"Good news I found something that should help make you less generic and more detailed. Thanks to the variety of average people here I can make shifts to what would be considered 'generic'. Unfortunately, I can't control it exactly so it will be random. so sorry about that."

[These will choose the specifics of your character. press each randomizer once.]

rows.title: points
rows.titleText:
"Alright first off we need to figure out how much points your soul is worth.Every soul has *charge* in it. This charge is comprised of all of the potential future and past choices and events that the person will ever make or experience. Since the world we're in is made from an anime the inhabitants don't make nearly as much choices and anything that happens after the books end only give them half as much charge. this means that we'll have to diffuse your soul so this dimension doesn't reject you.This means that I will turn your soul into points that you can make into items, abilities, and other important things." 

[choose one difficulty]

objects.title: Hard
objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

objects.title: Medium
objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

objects.title: Easy
objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

objects.title: Worldbreaker
objects.text:
"I'll be honest this option is blank on my side so I'd advise not touching it"

[do it]

addons.text: "What?! So much power should be impossible!!! Something must've gone wrong when I sent you to this world. With this much power the barriers between realities will start bleeding into each other. Expect stories to change and visitors from other worlds to appear randomly. even whole towns to appear out of nowhere."

objects.wordChangeSelect: What?! So much power should be impossible!!! Something must've gone wrong. with this much power the walls between worlds will start bleeding into each other. expect stories to change and visitors from other worlds.

rows.title: Drop-in location
rows.titleText: okay, this will be your first big choice. where are you? you might not notice yet but that haybale really isn't a good place to set up shop. Choosing may cost a little bit of energy so if you just let me drop you somewhere randomly then I can give you that energy as a little bonus.

objects.title: asakusa
objects.text: [North-east of central Tokyo Asakusa is a Heavily populated urban center with tall buildings and bright lights that illuminate the city during the night. a small trolley system runs through throughout. the city is fairly safe from demons since they would attract too much attention in such a crowded city. That doesn't mean that none have ever done it though.]

objects.title: yoshiwara
objects.text: [North of central Tokyo yoshiwara is a red light district with large amounts of courtesan survices and pleasure houses. the three most famous of this era are the Tokito house, the kyoguku house, and the Ogimoto house. The city is not known to host many demons but rumors have circulated about a beautiful and cruel oirannthat has lived for centuries.]

objects.title: swordsmith village
objects.text: [Located in a hyper-secured mountain range the swordsmith village is home to the craftsman who makes the Nichirin blades and their families. No one is allowed in or out without permission and an overly complicated system of blindfolded trips along a winding path. few know its true location and even fewer are still alive to tell. arriving here without warning will certainly raise some alarms]

objects.title: tanjiros village
objects.text: [A small rural village near Tanjiro's family home. it is a small and quiet village but that low-density population means that there is more of a chance for demon attacks]

objects.title: infinity castle
objects.text: [the home territory of the Demon King Muzan and his twelve demon moons. The castle is an infinitely expanding void made of wooden rooms and screen doors. the castle is controlled by the demon Nakime so it can rearrange itself into any configuration. gravity means little as it moves constantly allowing you to walk on walls and ceilings. there are only three likely possibilities when landing here. 1. an upper moon finds you and kills you 2. Muzan finds you and kills you 3.By some stroke of luck you are forcibly ejected by Nakime

objects.title: Ubuyashiki Estate
objects.text: [the home territory of the Demon Slayer's top brass. The estate itself is the home of the Ubuyashiki family including the head of the Slayers only known as Oyakata-sama aka "Master". The estates surrounding it are almost entirely owned by active and former hashira. so be careful if you arrive here uninvited

objects.title: Yakushima Island
objects.text: not japan proper, but a small island off of mainland Japan.  It is known for its dense forests and its thousand-year-old trees, the Yakusugi cedars.

objects.title: Boons
objects.text: "Alright now every choice under this section is a boon that will increase your chances of survival and make you stronger. so you'll need to use your soul points for them. certain combinations will give you even greater power so keep an eye out for them. Also, try not to end on a negative soul charge, or else you will implode, though I might be able to help a little bit as long as you don't go too crazy overboard. Now good luck"

rows.title: swords
rows.titleText: "Choose what type of weapon you use to fight demons. Don't worry no matter what weapon you use you will be able to incorporate it into your breathing style. There a couple of weapons that you should be able to duel wield"

objects.title: standard
objects.text: "The standard demon slayer corps sword. This is what you'd get if you just passed the entrance exam."

objects.title: legendary
objects.text: "A sword belonging to and passed down by a great swordsman of your breathing style. It is much stronger than a normal sword and also less likely to break"

objects.title: serrated
objects.text: "a standard sword that has been given a serrated edge that is better for shredding, sawing, and tearing through demons. Many swordsmiths might not take kindly to seeing this though, as the easiest way to make it is beating a standard sword with a rock until it cracks and bends."

objects.title: whip sword
objects.text: "The same type of sword that the love Hashira Mitsuri wields. Gives great range along with the ability to hit a larger radius, even targets that are behind you that you aren't facing."

objects.title: wakizashi
objects.text: "Typically used as a backup sword the wakizashi can be used with another katana as either as a spare or in tandem with another katana"  [can be taken with another weapon]

objects.title: poison tip
objects.text: "This blade has no cutting edge only a pointed tip that can pierce through enemies. this blade is ineffective unless paired with the proper fighting style"

objects.title: ShotGun
objects.text: "A wooden and steel shotgun that shoots Nichirin metal. The Slayer corps will only allow you to take this if you've proven yourself but can't use breathing."  [can be taken with another weapon]

objects.title: cleaver
objects.text: "The same pair of massive cleavers as used by the sound Hashira Tengen Uzui. . They can be used as either separate pieces or chained together to swing them around."

objects.title: serpentine
objects.text: "a snake-like blade as wielded by the snake Hashira Obanai Iguru. Its strange design is certainly confusing and hard to sheath but that confusion can be used to your advantage.

objects.title: axe and ball
objects.text: "An axe made of Nichirin metal. It is heavier then it looks and takes a truly great amount of strength to lift"

objects.title: knuckledusters
objects.text: "A pair of sharpened brass (or I guess I should say Nichirin)knuckles. These depend on how strong you are but they can land a pretty fair blow"

objects.title: Custom 1
objects.text: "You can also ask the smiths to make a custom blade. It must just be a normal blade but can be shaped however you want. you can also have it equipped differently (claw,shoe dagger, spear,etc)"

objects.title: custom 2
objects.text: "now your custom weapon can have multiple blades or a special function(poison tip, sparks, retractable chain,etc)"

objects.title: the ultimate duster
objects.text: "Is this even a blade? it looks just like a normal duster. Oh wait there's a note attached to it. (with this devastating tool a single swing can sweep up any filth). I guess you could really "clean up" the competition"

objects.title: kensuke
objects.text:
"A Sword that is balanced so that it can be wielded either one or two handedly. It also has an inner section that contains a mollusk-like creature that can sense when demons are near. 
[gives demon sense for free]

objects.title: Nichirin balls [jojo]
objects.text: "a pair of perfectly spherical Nichirin balls. if thrown properly they can inflict serious damage"

rows.title: Breathing styles
rows.titleText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.

objects.title: water Breathing
objects.text: Water Breathing is a Style that mimics the fluidity and grace of water. Most,  techniques involve the user moving in a fluid motion to match the movements of rushing or flowing water. This is the most common breathing style due to being the easiest to learn for beginners.

objects.title: flame Breathing
objects.text: Flame Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics flame's quick and everchanging motions. Most techniques involve rapid powerful singular strikes which 'burn' their opponents.

objects.title: Thunder Breathing
objects.text: Thunder Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics lightning's swift and deadly strikes with movements comparable to lightning ripping through the sky. Many techniques involve blinding speeds and immensely fast attacks that overwhelm the enemy in a small number of strikes.

objects.title: wind Breathing
objects.text: Wind Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics wind's powerful torrents and whirlwinds. Most techniques are powerful offensive attacks, many of which utilize rotating movements to generate swift whirlwind-like slashes that greatly increase the wielder's striking range.

objects.title: Beast Breathing
objects.text: Beast Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics the unpredictable, ferocious, and wild nature of wild animals. Most techniques are simple and straightforward with sudden unpredictable changes throwing enemies off guard.

objects.title: Stone Breathing
objects.text: Stone Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics the stability and strength of earth and stone. Most techniques utilize the ground beneath the user and their surroundings to generate powerful and sturdy attacks.

objects.title: Flower Breathing
objects.text: Flower Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics the grace and floatiness of flowers and fruit blossoms. Most, techniques are a combination of graceful and agile attacks. This Breathing Style also enhances and utilizes vision, albeit at the risk of damaged eyesight.

objects.title: insect Breathing
objects.text: Insect Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics the graceful flight and deadly stings of insects. Most techniques and forms include stabbing, thrusting, and making shallow cuts with a specially coated sword to inflict multiple wounds on the target and inject lethal wisteria-based poisons into them.

objects.title: serpent Breathing
objects.text: Serpent Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics the twisting slithering movements of snakes. Most techniques focus on twisting and bending the sword attacks are not direct and can ultimately strike anywhere.

objects.title: love Breathing
objects.text: Love Breathing is a Breathing Style that is based on the emotion of love, and replicates it with the user's movements and techniques use a gymnastic and movement-oriented rhythm to perform wide, winding and weaving slashes that have mid-to-long range applications.

objects.title: sound Breathing
objects.text: Sound Breathing is a Breathing Style that uses sound to disorient and control the flow of battle. Most techniques and forms utilize explosives to deal massive amounts of damage while making use of extremely fast movements that move so fast they create small sonic booms.

objects.title: mist Breathing
objects.text: Mist Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics mist's obscurity and gentle flow. Most techniques involve hidden movements and attacks that disorientate and confuse the target, similar to how a thick layer of mist obscures one's vision.

objects.title: combustion Breathing
objects.text: Combustion Breathing is a Breathing Style that mimics the rapid destructive movements of dynamite. Most techniques focus on rapid and unexpected strikes along with generating heat from the ferocity of your strikes.

objects.title: Original
objects.text: a breathing style of your very own. will you use quick decisive strikes? overwhelming power? targeted precision? whatever you use this style will continue to grow and evolve as you develop it on your own.

objects.title: Hamon Breathing
objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

objects.title: Ki breathing
objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

objects.title: Steel breathing
objects.text: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.

rows.title: Breathing Combos
rows.titleText: "real quickly there are a couple of breathing styles that heavily benefit from having the proper sword so let's see if you have the proper combinations"

objects.title: true insect breathing
objects.text: [requires poison tip and insect breathing]

objects.title: true beast breathing
objects.text: [requires serrated blade and beast breathing]

objects.title: true love breathing
objects.text: [requires whip sword and love breathing]

objects.title: true serpent breathing
objects.text: [requires serpent sword and serpent breathing]

objects.title: true stone breathing
objects.text: [requires ball and chain and stone breathing]

objects.title: dragon power
objects.text:
"A combination of the two Ki abilities. It seems that the more you train the stronger you get with no upper limit. though it does seem that at some point you will need some truly insane levels of training equipment to advance."

[Requires Ki claymore and ki breathing]

objects.title: stand power
objects.text:
"was that a shimmer behind you? Strange it appears as though you have some sort of guardian spirit now. People without a stand won't be able to see it but you will certainly find people who can. whether they're friendly or not is another question."
[Requires Hamon and Anubis] 
[gives a close-range stand equal to or lesser than Stone Free.]
[gives trouble magnet]

objects.title: stand power
objects.text:
"pppppp "
[Requires Hamon and pluck]

objects.title: Nope
objects.text: "hey, that's okay even if you dont have a combination you can still become very powerful."

rows.title: Abilities
rows.titleText: "Alright this section is for things that aren't part of your breathing style but that would still give you better chances of survival in a fight or other such bonuses."

objects.title: sense of sight
objects.text: "With this ability, you will not only have great vision, being able to see long distances, but you will also be able to see motion much clearer even in pitch dark."

objects.title: sense of smell
objects.text:
"With this ability you will have an amazing sense of smell. with practice you will be able to tell where different smells are coming from and what type of smell it is just from a quick whiff"
[if a smell is unimportant to you you can block it out unless it changes or is too putrid]

objects.title: sense of hearing
objects.text:
"With this ability you will be able to hear a pin drop from a mile away, a mutter underneath someone's breath, a heartbeat from any major distance, etc etc. You will also be able to sense which direction any sound is coming from" 
[You can also decrease your hearing to normal levels to prevent yourself from going insane from constant stimulation]

objects.title: sense of touch
objects.text:
"With this ability you will be able to feel small changes to what you're feeling. shifts in the wind on your skin, changes in material, weak points in hard objects, etc" 
[this only works for when you are actively trying to feel something. you won't feel everything unless you want to]

objects.title: demon sense
objects.text:
"this is more intuition then truly a sense but I still think It counts. basically you'll be able to tell when a demon is within a certain range of you, even if you can't actually sense them with any other sense" 
[you now can sense the rough location of any demon within a 5 mile radius.]

objects.title: Total awareness
objects.text:
"This ability works by using all of your heightened senses(except for taste...yuck) to get a near perfect sense of your surroundings even with your eyes closed. you can visualize this as a 3d map in your head where everything is shades of grey."  

[requires all senses to be selected]

objects.title: hyper dense muscles
objects.text:
"This makes you much stronger because there are more muscles in your muscles? I'll be honest I never understood this but it's a thing that can happen in this world so it's an option" 

[with increased muscle mass your strength skyrockets]

objects.title: hard headed
objects.text:
"a skull of steel!! ok not literally but you're head will be so much stronger now. and as an added bonus I'll throw in reduced headaches and you'll never get a concussion." 

[gives you tanjiros hard head]

objects.title: creative
objects.text:
you find it a lot easier to some up with creative solutions to problems. whether that's how to stop a squeaky hinge or how to lop off a demons head the solution will come easier to you.
[gives you tanjiros hard head]

rows.title: drawbacks
rows.titleText: "hhmmm that's not good. you need more points. well I should be able to give you more, but it will cost you. what. just because its *my* fault you expect me to help you more than I already have?... ... ... Make sure not to take too many drawbacks or you may not be able to live a very fulfilling life. Some drawbacks might even effect your strength so watch out."

objects.title: short of breath
objects.text: "With this you'll get winded easier. No matter how hard you train you'll always run out of breath a bit quicker than you should."

objects.title: Breathless
objects.text: "With this you'll lose your breathe even easier. even a short training session will have you huffing and puffing."

objects.title: Capped strength
objects.text: "while other people may be able to grow with training you will never advance past your current strength. you can still learn techniques but you will never be physically stronger than you are now"

objects.title: Unteachable
objects.text: "With this choice you will never be able to learn or create new techniques. You can grow physically stronger but will never be able to use anything except what you already know."

objects.title: Rage
objects.text: "Now you'll be much more emotional. even the slightest insult can set you off. be careful not to get distracted when fighting or your temper could cost you dearly."

objects.title: Immortality
objects.text: "I am so sorry!! I messed up even though I know that no mortal deserves this, not even you!! I made a mistake when applying your plot armor so now you're immortal. Truly fully immortal. you will still feel every blow and every injury, you will live until the day the sun implodes and after. I cannot tell you how sorry I am. I hope you find it in yourself to forgive me someday"

objects.title: who are you?
objects.text: "okay this one feels a bit rude since your already here but this will make you forget anything you knew about this world before you got here. any advantage you had from preexisting knowledge is gone"

objects.title: who were you?
objects.text: "okay this one does the same but to the extreme. Now you will forget everything you knew before coming to this world. you will still be the same person but you won't remember where you came from or how you got here."
"There's something about you that demons really want. Any demon in a 50 mile radius. knows where you are and will slowly start moving towards you every night."

objects.title: targeted
objects.text: "a specific demon wants you dead. it is fairly strong. about that of the arrow or ball demons "

objects.title: Nemesis
objects.text: "Now you've really annoyed some top brass. An upper moon actively wants you dead. Its not the most important thing on their list, but they know you by name and want you gone."

objects.title: Devils enemy
objects.text: "MUZAN!!!? Muzan wants you dead personally. He fears you as much as he does the kamado family. you'd better be very strong if you want to survive this."

objects.title: HE'S GOTTA SWORD
objects.text: "People will probably already freak out a bit if they see you carrying your sword around, but now they'll assume that you've killed someone the second they see it."

objects.title: trouble magnet
objects.text: "Trouble will find you always. it might be a demon or it might just be an angry neighbor. though in certain circumstances, it could be something even worse"

objects.title: paper skin & brittle bones
objects.text: "Now when you get injured it will take a lot longer for you to heal. a simple paper cut could take a month to fully close."

objects.title: Traitor
objects.text: "Ah. that's not good. The Slayer Corps consider you a traitor. now you won't be able to use any of their resources. So no new swords, no wisteria,  and no medical help."

objects.title: temptations
objects.text: "This is somewhat the opposite of Nemesis. now any moon demon will try and bring you over to the side of demons. If you accept this offer than the demon will try and convince muzan to transform you, but if he decides not to he will kill you right away."

objects.title: True demon
objects.text:
"Now you are an actual demon. The sunlight burns you and contact with nichirin or wisteria hurts you. You also can't use breathing as your internal organs no longer function, but don't think that just because you're a demon don't think you can stop your hunter duties. you'll still have to fight demons but now no one will help you. no slayers, no humans, and no demons will ever be on your side. I would highly advise against taking this drawback."

[cannot take a breathing style or a weapon with this choice]

rows.title: final combos
rows.titleText:
[one final box hovers in front of you]

"oh this is strange. you should be finished and on your way but I guess that a couple of your drawbacks, abilities,etc have formed something even I was unaware of. I can't affect these combos so please take as many or as few as you want"

[choose more combos]

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
